00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Downloaded From www.AllSubs.org

1
00:02:32,118 --> 00:02:36,316
Quiet, Mirza.
Mirza, quiet now.

2
00:02:36,389 --> 00:02:39,085
Afternoon, madame.

3
00:02:39,158 --> 00:02:41,149
- Yes, what is it?
- I'm sorry to bother you.

4
00:02:41,227 --> 00:02:44,424
I was told about an apartment.

5
00:02:48,734 --> 00:02:51,464
This is the right building
though, isn't it?

6
00:02:51,537 --> 00:02:53,471
Who told you?

7
00:02:53,539 --> 00:02:55,564
A friend of mine.

8
00:02:55,641 --> 00:02:58,371
Uh, well, a relation, actually.

9
00:02:58,444 --> 00:03:00,639
- The door.
- Sorry.

10
00:03:01,814 --> 00:03:04,044
I gather it's a small
two-room apartment.

11
00:03:04,116 --> 00:03:06,050
Think that's all I got to do?

12
00:03:06,118 --> 00:03:09,053
Some people think a concierge
is a slave.

13
00:03:09,121 --> 00:03:11,055
Not me, not me, I assure you.

14
00:03:11,123 --> 00:03:13,853
Would it be more convenient
if I came back later?

15
00:03:13,926 --> 00:03:17,453
Anyway, you have to
speak with Monsieur Zy.

16
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:20,931
- I can only show the apartment.
- I don't want to be a nuisance...

17
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,128
but if it were at all possible...

18
00:03:24,203 --> 00:03:27,707
and if I might offer you some...

19
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:31,139
small compensation for your
trouble which is only reasonable.

20
00:03:36,248 --> 00:03:39,046
What a lovely little doggie you are.

21
00:03:39,118 --> 00:03:41,518
You're Mirza, aren't you?

22
00:03:43,589 --> 00:03:46,456
It's a nice name, Mirza.

23
00:03:58,871 --> 00:04:00,805
I'm sorry.

24
00:05:19,218 --> 00:05:21,846
The previous tenant
threw herself out of the window.

25
00:05:25,424 --> 00:05:27,358
You can still see where she fell.

26
00:05:29,195 --> 00:05:31,129
Look.

27
00:05:35,401 --> 00:05:37,528
He's gonna have to fix that.

28
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:42,096
She's not dead yet...

29
00:05:42,174 --> 00:05:44,267
though she might as well be.

30
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:47,642
She's in the Bretonneau hospital.

31
00:05:47,713 --> 00:05:50,204
What if she gets better?

32
00:05:50,282 --> 00:05:53,080
Don't worry.
She won't get better.

33
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:55,484
You know,
you're onto a good thing here.

34
00:05:55,554 --> 00:05:58,648
Poor woman.
What are the terms? Do you know?

35
00:05:58,724 --> 00:06:01,625
Well, there's a fee for the water.
All the plumbing is new.

36
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:04,424
You used to have to go out
to the landing to get water.

37
00:06:04,496 --> 00:06:06,430
- And the toilet?
- It's right over there.

38
00:06:06,498 --> 00:06:09,956
You just go around the corridor,
and there it is.

39
00:06:10,035 --> 00:06:13,732
That's a view worth looking at.

40
00:06:18,577 --> 00:06:20,511
How much is the premium?

41
00:06:20,579 --> 00:06:23,173
The rent is 600 francs a month.

42
00:06:23,249 --> 00:06:26,582
Uh, the premium,
I'm not sure about.

43
00:06:26,652 --> 00:06:29,917
I think he wants 5,000 francs.

44
00:06:29,989 --> 00:06:33,550
Five thousand?
That's a lot of money.

45
00:06:33,626 --> 00:06:37,323
It's not my business. For that
you'll have to talk to Monsieur Zy.

46
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:39,330
He lives right down here.

47
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:43,660
I have to get back now.

48
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,702
All right, all right.
We're not deaf.

49
00:07:19,872 --> 00:07:23,239
- We don't give to charity.
- It's about the apartment.

50
00:07:23,309 --> 00:07:25,243
What apartment?

51
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:29,407
On the floor above.
Could I speak to Monsieur Zy?

52
00:07:59,712 --> 00:08:01,646
Afternoon.

53
00:08:12,725 --> 00:08:13,987
Have you seen the apartment?

54
00:08:14,059 --> 00:08:17,995
Yes. That's why I wanted to talk
to you, to discuss the terms.

55
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:23,266
Five thousand premium,
six hundred a month.

56
00:08:23,335 --> 00:08:27,066
That's a lot of money.
I couldn't pay more than 4,000.

57
00:08:31,977 --> 00:08:33,968
The concierge told you
about the water?

58
00:08:34,046 --> 00:08:36,708
Yes, she did.

59
00:08:36,782 --> 00:08:40,149
It's damned hard to find
an apartment these days, you know.

60
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:42,153
There's a student up
on the sixth floor...

61
00:08:42,221 --> 00:08:44,781
gave me half that much
for a single room.

62
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:48,759
Don't get me wrong. I'm not trying
to criticize your apartment...

63
00:08:48,827 --> 00:08:51,193
but the toilet is a problem.

64
00:08:51,263 --> 00:08:55,393
Suppose I got sick-- which I don't
often do, I can assure you--

65
00:08:55,467 --> 00:08:58,300
and I had to relieve myself
in the middle of the night.

66
00:08:59,471 --> 00:09:01,666
It wouldn't be
very convenient, would it?

67
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:06,939
On the other hand, I could pay you
the 4,000 right away, in cash.

68
00:09:07,012 --> 00:09:09,310
It's not only a question
of the money.

69
00:09:09,381 --> 00:09:12,544
- Let's be clear, Monsieur--
- Trelkovsky.

70
00:09:14,153 --> 00:09:16,348
Trelkovsky.

71
00:09:16,422 --> 00:09:19,789
I won't exactly starve
without your 5,000.

72
00:09:19,858 --> 00:09:22,292
No. I'm renting the apartment
because it's vacant...

73
00:09:22,361 --> 00:09:24,795
and because I know
they don't grow on trees.

74
00:09:24,863 --> 00:09:26,797
Of course, Monsieur Zy.

75
00:09:26,865 --> 00:09:29,299
It's perfectly reasonable.
I understand your point.

76
00:09:29,368 --> 00:09:31,928
Could I offer you a cigarette?

77
00:09:32,004 --> 00:09:34,131
You want 5,000, fine.

78
00:09:34,206 --> 00:09:37,972
But if you got paid by check,
you'd have to declare it.

79
00:09:38,043 --> 00:09:41,308
Wouldn't you rather
get 4,000 in cash?

80
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:44,975
I'd rather get 5,000 in cash
than 4,000 in cash.

81
00:09:47,419 --> 00:09:49,353
It's perfectly natural.

82
00:09:49,421 --> 00:09:53,255
Anyway, the former tenant
is not dead yet.

83
00:09:53,325 --> 00:09:57,022
If she comes back, you won't even
get your 4,000. You get nothing.

84
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:59,564
Are you married?
Excuse the question...

85
00:09:59,631 --> 00:10:01,861
but it's because of the children.

86
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:04,494
This is a very quiet building.

87
00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:08,563
- My wife and I are getting on--
- I wouldn't say that, Monsieur Zy.

88
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:10,073
I know what I'm saying.

89
00:10:10,142 --> 00:10:12,702
My wife and I are getting on.
We don't like a lot of noise.

90
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:14,712
You needn't worry, Monsieur Zy.

91
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:17,340
I am very quiet myself,
and I am a bachelor.

92
00:10:18,851 --> 00:10:21,718
Bachelors can be a problem too.

93
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:25,223
If you're looking for a place
to entertain your girlfriends...

94
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:28,094
I'd rather take 2,000 and give
it to somebody who really needs it.

95
00:10:28,227 --> 00:10:31,128
I quite agree,
but I am not that type.

96
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:33,927
Well now, I can't give you
a definite answer...

97
00:10:33,999 --> 00:10:37,560
while Mademoiselle Choule
is still alive.

98
00:10:37,636 --> 00:10:39,763
But I like you.

99
00:10:39,839 --> 00:10:42,740
You seem to be
a serious young man to me.

100
00:10:59,191 --> 00:11:02,683
I want to visit
Mademoiselle Choule.

101
00:11:11,203 --> 00:11:13,137
- Simone Choule?
- That's right.

102
00:11:13,205 --> 00:11:16,140
- Are you a relative?
- I'm a friend.

103
00:11:28,053 --> 00:11:30,487
Can I help you?

104
00:11:30,556 --> 00:11:32,581
- Are you the head nurse, ma'am?
- Yes.

105
00:11:32,658 --> 00:11:34,091
I'm very glad I found you...

106
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,594
because I was told at the
reception desk to see you first.

107
00:11:36,662 --> 00:11:40,826
- It's about Mademoiselle Choule.
- Bed 18.

108
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,630
- May I see her?
- She's not to be disturbed.

109
00:11:43,702 --> 00:11:45,863
She was in a coma till yesterday.

110
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:48,406
Go ahead,
but don't try to talk to her.

111
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:31,314
Are you a friend of hers?

112
00:12:31,383 --> 00:12:33,613
Excuse me.

113
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:43,053
I can't believe it.
I just can't believe it.

114
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:46,560
I was with her the night before.

115
00:12:46,632 --> 00:12:49,362
No, two nights before.

116
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,665
She was in such good spirits.

117
00:12:53,772 --> 00:12:56,104
Why would she do a thing like that?

118
00:12:56,175 --> 00:12:58,973
To tell you the truth,
I'm not a close-- I--

119
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:01,478
I hardly know her at all,
actually, but believe me...

120
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:03,481
I'm terribly upset about...

121
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:05,483
- Yeah.
- what's happened.

122
00:13:06,752 --> 00:13:08,686
It's awful.

123
00:13:09,989 --> 00:13:14,449
Simone? Simone.

124
00:13:14,526 --> 00:13:19,554
You do recognize me, don't you?
It's me, Stella.

125
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,999
Your friend, Stella.

126
00:13:23,068 --> 00:13:25,593
Don't you recognize me?

127
00:13:35,347 --> 00:13:37,338
You'll have to leave now.

128
00:13:37,416 --> 00:13:39,577
Your bag.

129
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,120
Is there any hope of saving her?

130
00:13:42,187 --> 00:13:45,554
What do you mean?
If we can save her, we save her.

131
00:14:10,249 --> 00:14:13,650
Careful. You mustn't
give in to your grief.

132
00:14:15,454 --> 00:14:19,982
Huh? If you like, we could go
and have something to drink.

133
00:14:20,059 --> 00:14:21,993
I think it would help you.

134
00:14:23,462 --> 00:14:25,396
There is a--

135
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:36,368
Here.

136
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:48,142
What would you like to drink?

137
00:14:50,289 --> 00:14:52,223
I don't know.

138
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:55,351
I'll have, uh, beer. No, a coffee.

139
00:14:55,427 --> 00:14:57,657
Coffee. And the lady?

140
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:59,664
I don't want a coffee.

141
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:03,168
You should have something strong.
It will pick you up.

142
00:15:03,235 --> 00:15:05,703
I'll have a small glass
of Beaujolais.

143
00:15:05,771 --> 00:15:08,467
A small glass of Beaujolais and...

144
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,735
- a Martini.
- No coffee?

145
00:15:10,809 --> 00:15:12,743
No, no, a Martini.

146
00:15:17,816 --> 00:15:20,410
I completely forgot!
I have a phone call to make.

147
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:24,745
I'll be right back.

148
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:43,897
- Waiter!
- All right, I'm coming.

149
00:15:46,645 --> 00:15:48,943
I'll never understand suicide.

150
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:55,386
I have no argument against it,
but it's beyond my comprehension.

151
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:59,716
Did you ever discuss it with her?

152
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,657
Never.

153
00:16:02,828 --> 00:16:05,160
I just can't believe it.

154
00:16:06,665 --> 00:16:09,657
It's terrible. Terrible.

155
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,433
It's terrible, yeah.

156
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:14,904
Could it have been
a disappointment in love, perhaps?

157
00:16:14,973 --> 00:16:17,806
- Something like that?
- Who with?

158
00:16:17,876 --> 00:16:19,810
I don't know. Some man.

159
00:16:20,879 --> 00:16:22,813
You know she wasn't
interested in men.

160
00:16:24,516 --> 00:16:27,679
Oh, yes, I know, but--

161
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:31,450
Women as sensitive as she was--
as she is, I mean--

162
00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:33,457
often tend to have...

163
00:16:33,525 --> 00:16:38,087
much more complicated relationships
than they seem to.

164
00:16:39,798 --> 00:16:42,665
Perhaps she will pull out
of it anyway.

165
00:16:42,734 --> 00:16:45,464
I doubt it.

166
00:16:45,537 --> 00:16:49,473
Did you notice that she didn't
even recognize me?

167
00:16:51,543 --> 00:16:53,272
A tragedy.

168
00:16:57,549 --> 00:17:00,382
Hey, man, you got any bread
for an artist?

169
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,624
I don't seem to have any change.

170
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,626
I don't care.
I'll take what you got.

171
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,457
There, you see?
I've only got notes.

172
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:12,997
Come on. You don't wanna look cheap
in front of your girlfriend.

173
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:17,535
Not a word of thanks.
Did you notice?

174
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:19,537
I don't like tramps.

175
00:17:19,605 --> 00:17:22,597
You shouldn't have
given him anything.

176
00:19:02,005 --> 00:19:04,439
Would you like to have a drink?

177
00:19:04,507 --> 00:19:07,101
No, thanks.

178
00:19:07,177 --> 00:19:09,304
Right.

179
00:19:09,379 --> 00:19:11,108
- Good-bye, then.
- Good-bye.

180
00:19:11,181 --> 00:19:13,308
Hope to see you soon.

181
00:19:31,768 --> 00:19:35,704
- What is it?
-Just came over from CNMA.

182
00:19:35,772 --> 00:19:39,173
- Was it sent by Monsieur Lott?
- Uh-huh, Monsieur Lott. Right.

183
00:19:39,242 --> 00:19:41,210
That must be
the Villa LeDuc, then.

184
00:19:41,277 --> 00:19:43,507
Yes, that's right.

185
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:47,710
Yeah, that's the Villa LeDuc.
"Unmounted, number 2601.

186
00:19:47,784 --> 00:19:51,311
"Make detailed copy of spire
in the lower left-hand corner...

187
00:19:51,388 --> 00:19:53,822
beside the registration number."

188
00:19:53,890 --> 00:19:55,824
You have to do it by next Thursday.

189
00:20:32,262 --> 00:20:34,196
I'm calling to ask you
if you have any news...

190
00:20:34,264 --> 00:20:36,789
about Mademoiselle Simone Choule.

191
00:20:36,866 --> 00:20:40,199
<i>- What department is she in?
- Surgery.</i>

192
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:43,205
<i>- Choule? With a C?
- That's right.</i>

193
00:20:43,273 --> 00:20:46,208
<i>- Simone Choule.
-Are you a relative?</i>

194
00:20:46,276 --> 00:20:49,507
No, I'm a friend.

195
00:20:49,579 --> 00:20:52,810
<i>The patient died
at 4:20 p.m.yesterday.</i>

196
00:20:55,852 --> 00:20:57,786
Thank you.

197
00:21:00,323 --> 00:21:01,756
Good-bye.

198
00:25:23,186 --> 00:25:25,313
- Morning, monsieur.
- Morning.

199
00:25:25,388 --> 00:25:27,322
Live opposite?

200
00:25:27,390 --> 00:25:29,517
Yes. I just moved in.

201
00:25:29,592 --> 00:25:34,029
You rented the apartment of that
girl that jumped out of the window?

202
00:25:34,096 --> 00:25:38,829
-Yes. Did you know her?
-Sure, I did. Came in every morning.

203
00:25:38,901 --> 00:25:43,668
Always sat in the same place.
Right there where you are now.

204
00:25:43,739 --> 00:25:46,799
A cup of chocolate and a roll
and butter. Never drank coffee.

205
00:25:46,876 --> 00:25:51,813
Used to say, "If I have a coffee,
I can't sleep for two days."

206
00:25:51,881 --> 00:25:55,044
- Question of what you're used to.
- Shall I make you a chocolate?

207
00:25:55,117 --> 00:25:57,381
A question of temperament too,
I think.

208
00:25:57,453 --> 00:26:00,217
Still, a young girl
like that killing herself.

209
00:26:00,289 --> 00:26:01,756
I can't imagine why.

210
00:26:01,824 --> 00:26:04,418
No reason at all, probably.

211
00:26:04,493 --> 00:26:08,589
A moment of depression,
and wham, it's all over.

212
00:26:11,701 --> 00:26:12,633
Robert.

213
00:26:38,794 --> 00:26:40,386
Do you sell cigarettes?

214
00:26:40,463 --> 00:26:43,955
- Yes. What would you like?
- Gauloises Bleu, please.

215
00:26:44,033 --> 00:26:46,558
Oh. I'm right out of Gauloises.

216
00:26:46,636 --> 00:26:49,366
- Oh, what else do you have?
- Gitanes, Marlboro.

217
00:26:49,438 --> 00:26:52,669
Mademoiselle Choule always smoked
Marlboro. Would you like a pack?

218
00:26:53,676 --> 00:26:55,473
No. No, thank you.

219
00:27:35,685 --> 00:27:40,349
Simone Choule, the Lord
has taken thee to his bosom...

220
00:27:40,423 --> 00:27:44,450
just as a shepherd brings in
his sheep at the close of day.

221
00:27:44,527 --> 00:27:48,429
What could be more natural,
of greater consolation?

222
00:27:48,497 --> 00:27:50,931
Is it not the fondest hope
and desire of all of us...

223
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:54,766
that we shall one day
rejoin the flock of holy ones?

224
00:27:54,837 --> 00:27:58,295
Hope of eternal life?
The true life?

225
00:27:58,374 --> 00:28:01,775
Shorn of all worldly cares?

226
00:28:01,844 --> 00:28:05,974
Face to face in eternal
blessedness with Almighty God...

227
00:28:06,048 --> 00:28:08,243
who through his son
our Lord Jesus Christ...

228
00:28:08,317 --> 00:28:12,720
died for us on the cross.

229
00:28:12,788 --> 00:28:16,019
Who deigns to look down upon us
poor mortal creatures...

230
00:28:16,092 --> 00:28:18,526
full of love,
infinitely merciful...

231
00:28:18,594 --> 00:28:23,031
the sick, the suffering, the dying.

232
00:28:23,099 --> 00:28:27,092
Yes, the dying. The icy tomb.

233
00:28:27,169 --> 00:28:31,697
Thou shalt return to the dust
from whence thou came...

234
00:28:31,774 --> 00:28:33,935
and only thy bones remain.

235
00:28:34,009 --> 00:28:36,136
The worms shall consume thy eyes...

236
00:28:36,212 --> 00:28:39,648
thy lips, thy mouth.

237
00:28:39,715 --> 00:28:44,209
They shall enter into thy ears.
They shall enter into thy nostrils.

238
00:28:44,286 --> 00:28:47,687
Thy body shall putrefy
unto its innermost recesses...

239
00:28:47,757 --> 00:28:50,726
and shall give off
a noisome stench.

240
00:28:50,793 --> 00:28:53,921
Yea, Christ is ascended
into heaven and hath joined...

241
00:28:53,996 --> 00:28:58,057
the host of angels on high,
but not for creeps like you...

242
00:28:58,134 --> 00:29:00,329
full of the basest vice...

243
00:29:00,403 --> 00:29:04,533
yearning only for
carnal satisfaction.

244
