ever daring to say anything.

476
00:54:45,545 --> 00:54:49,447
I acted as though we were
just friends each time I saw her--

477
00:54:49,516 --> 00:54:52,849
which wasn't very often,
I can tell you that.

478
00:54:54,587 --> 00:54:57,078
It just isn't fair.

479
00:54:57,157 --> 00:55:01,184
The day I summon up enough
courage to tell her...

480
00:55:01,261 --> 00:55:03,559
I find out--

481
00:55:03,630 --> 00:55:06,190
I find out she's--

482
00:55:12,105 --> 00:55:14,630
Why?

483
00:55:14,707 --> 00:55:17,699
Why didn't I ever tell her?

484
00:55:18,912 --> 00:55:22,575
She's gone without ever knowing it.

485
00:55:22,649 --> 00:55:25,117
We'll be closing now,
Monsieur Trelkovsky.

486
00:55:25,185 --> 00:55:27,949
- Yeah.
- Life isn't worth living anymore.

487
00:55:28,021 --> 00:55:30,285
- You mustn't--
- That'll be six francs sixty.

488
00:55:30,356 --> 00:55:33,792
You mustn't think like that.
You're young. You'll forget.

489
00:55:35,962 --> 00:55:37,395
Wait.

490
00:55:39,399 --> 00:55:41,367
Wait a minute!

491
00:55:42,836 --> 00:55:44,770
Thank you.

492
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:56,675
I can promise you
she didn't suffer.

493
00:55:57,750 --> 00:56:00,742
And she didn't say anything?

494
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:03,414
- You sure?
- Absolutely certain.

495
00:56:05,090 --> 00:56:07,024
All right, all right.

496
00:56:08,928 --> 00:56:11,522
It's my round,
for Christ's sakes.

497
00:56:11,597 --> 00:56:13,360
Drinks for everyone!

498
00:56:22,341 --> 00:56:24,172
Everyone except him.

499
00:56:38,257 --> 00:56:43,058
Don't mind him.
He's drunk. Drunk.

500
00:56:43,128 --> 00:56:47,394
- What you've done for me--
- It's natural.

501
00:56:47,466 --> 00:56:51,926
- It's not natural at all.
- It is natural.

502
00:56:52,004 --> 00:56:57,067
There aren't many guys around
like you. It's as simple as this.

503
00:57:00,179 --> 00:57:02,113
You saved my life.

504
00:57:25,671 --> 00:57:27,400
- Morning.
- Good morning.

505
00:57:30,743 --> 00:57:33,439
A cup of chocolate,
Monsieur Trelkovsky?

506
00:57:33,512 --> 00:57:35,104
Why not?

507
00:57:45,057 --> 00:57:46,991
Could I have some
Gauloises Bleu, please?

508
00:57:47,059 --> 00:57:48,651
Yes.

509
00:57:59,838 --> 00:58:03,467
Mmm. I wanted some Gauloises.

510
00:58:03,542 --> 00:58:06,739
- Gauloises Bleu.
- I thought you said Marlboro.

511
00:58:06,812 --> 00:58:11,943
I've run out of Gauloises.
I'll send Robert out for some.

512
00:58:12,017 --> 00:58:15,043
Don't bother.
I'll take the Marlboro.

513
00:59:31,774 --> 00:59:34,368
- A pack of Marlboros.
- Gimme a pack of Gauloises.

514
00:59:36,279 --> 00:59:38,372
A pack of Marlboros, please.

515
00:59:46,022 --> 00:59:48,991
- Pack of Gauloises.
- Eight franc sixty.

516
00:59:53,096 --> 00:59:54,961
Okay, see ya next week.

517
01:00:22,992 --> 01:00:25,392
Hello! How are you?

518
01:00:25,461 --> 01:00:28,692
Very well, thanks. I was just going
to buy some cigarettes.

519
01:00:28,765 --> 01:00:31,632
Come and join us.
These are some friends of mine.

520
01:00:31,701 --> 01:00:34,568
- May I?
- Of course.

521
01:00:34,637 --> 01:00:37,105
- Hi.
- Hi.

522
01:00:40,243 --> 01:00:43,178
We were just
talking about Simone.

523
01:00:43,246 --> 01:00:45,476
- Simone?
- Simone Choule.

524
01:00:47,550 --> 01:00:51,247
This is the guy I told you about--
the one I met at the hospital.

525
01:00:51,321 --> 01:00:55,781
- We were the last to see her alive.
- Stella told us...

526
01:00:55,858 --> 01:00:58,588
Simone didn't seem
to know her.

527
01:00:58,661 --> 01:01:00,925
- I don't think she did.
- And you?

528
01:01:00,997 --> 01:01:05,195
- Me?
- She didn't recognize you either?

529
01:01:06,269 --> 01:01:08,794
It's hard to say.

530
01:01:08,871 --> 01:01:12,307
I couldn't be sure
one way or the other.

531
01:01:12,375 --> 01:01:16,141
Perhaps she was trying to say
something when she screamed.

532
01:01:17,914 --> 01:01:22,544
Anyway, that's the impression
I get when I think back on it.

533
01:01:24,153 --> 01:01:27,316
She was looking at you
when she let out that cry.

534
01:01:29,759 --> 01:01:31,886
- You think so?
- You know...

535
01:01:31,961 --> 01:01:36,694
I still have some things of hers
at home. It's depressing.

536
01:01:36,766 --> 01:01:41,032
- What've you got of hers?
- Some books, a couple of records.

537
01:01:48,211 --> 01:01:50,543
There's one of Simone's books.

538
01:01:58,621 --> 01:02:00,987
- I haven't read it.
- Nor have I.

539
01:02:01,057 --> 01:02:03,753
I'm not interested
in Egyptology.

540
01:02:03,826 --> 01:02:08,229
She left it behind one evening.
You can have it if you like.

541
01:02:08,898 --> 01:02:12,197
Oh, you're very kind.
I would love to read it.

542
01:02:17,338 --> 01:02:19,465
It's a magnificent place
you've got here.

543
01:02:19,540 --> 01:02:21,974
Better than where I live,
I can tell you.

544
01:02:25,914 --> 01:02:29,974
Sorry, if you don't mind me
asking, is the rent very high?

545
01:02:30,050 --> 01:02:33,884
I don't pay for it.
It belongs to my brother.

546
01:02:33,954 --> 01:02:39,824
He's gone off to Peru
for a few months, a year, traveling.

547
01:02:39,893 --> 01:02:41,485
Look, this track.

548
01:02:46,499 --> 01:02:49,024
Do you have any trouble
with your neighbors?

549
01:02:49,101 --> 01:02:50,534
What sort of trouble?

550
01:02:50,603 --> 01:02:53,003
Well, you know...

551
01:02:53,072 --> 01:02:56,734
these days, relationships
with neighbors can get...

552
01:02:56,808 --> 01:02:59,072
quite complicated.

553
01:02:59,144 --> 01:03:05,708
You know, little things that get
blown up out of all proportion.

554
01:03:05,784 --> 01:03:07,411
You know what I mean?

555
01:03:07,485 --> 01:03:10,578
No. No, I don't.

556
01:03:11,622 --> 01:03:13,556
I mind my own business.

557
01:03:17,361 --> 01:03:20,194
So do I.
It's the best way.

558
01:03:22,999 --> 01:03:25,331
If you like,
I'll take you home.

559
01:03:44,653 --> 01:03:47,985
Shall we go back
to your place?

560
01:03:48,056 --> 01:03:50,320
My place?

561
01:03:55,396 --> 01:03:57,330
Okay?

562
01:03:57,398 --> 01:03:59,332
Sure. Fine.

563
01:04:01,635 --> 01:04:05,571
Only my place is a bit--

564
01:04:05,639 --> 01:04:08,233
Well, it's a bit difficult.

565
01:04:08,308 --> 01:04:12,335
- In fact, it's impossible.
- Why?

566
01:04:12,412 --> 01:04:15,574
- Have you got a girlfriend?
- No.

567
01:04:15,648 --> 01:04:17,878
Not exactly.

568
01:04:17,950 --> 01:04:23,149
It's just that I've been repainting,
and the place is in chaos.

569
01:04:24,890 --> 01:04:28,882
We could still spend
a couple of hours there, hmm?

570
01:04:28,960 --> 01:04:33,556
On top of that, my uncle is
just up from the country...

571
01:04:33,631 --> 01:04:35,929
staying a few days.

572
01:04:40,070 --> 01:04:42,334
How about your place?

573
01:04:51,014 --> 01:04:53,277
Take off your coat.

574
01:05:05,428 --> 01:05:07,827
I'll be right back.

575
01:05:31,685 --> 01:05:33,549
I'd love something to drink.

576
01:05:40,527 --> 01:05:42,017
Cheers.

577
01:05:43,530 --> 01:05:44,996
Cheers.

578
01:05:53,972 --> 01:05:56,202
Why don't you
take your tie off?

579
01:05:56,275 --> 01:05:59,004
You look like you're
choking to death.

580
01:06:01,312 --> 01:06:04,372
I found a tooth
in my apartment.

581
01:06:04,449 --> 01:06:07,316
- It was in a hole.
- A tooth?

582
01:06:08,920 --> 01:06:10,854
In a hole?

583
01:06:10,922 --> 01:06:14,948
Yeah.
A hole in the wall.

584
01:06:15,025 --> 01:06:17,653
Wrapped in cotton wool.

585
01:06:17,727 --> 01:06:22,460
So? No need to pull
such a long face over a tooth.

586
01:06:23,700 --> 01:06:25,633
Pretty weird, though, isn't it?

587
01:06:27,970 --> 01:06:30,336
Not really.

588
01:06:30,406 --> 01:06:33,671
When I was young,
we did it all the time.

589
01:06:33,742 --> 01:06:36,677
Whenever one of my teeth
fell out...

590
01:06:36,745 --> 01:06:39,440
I used to hide it.

591
01:06:39,514 --> 01:06:43,382
My mother said it would
turn into a coin.

592
01:06:43,451 --> 01:06:45,214
A coin.

593
01:06:51,792 --> 01:06:53,987
Oh, God.

594
01:06:54,061 --> 01:06:56,928
- Stella, I was wondering--
- Yeah?

595
01:06:56,997 --> 01:06:58,430
Tooth--

596
01:07:01,134 --> 01:07:03,795
Tooth is a part of ourselves,
isn't it?

597
01:07:03,870 --> 01:07:08,466
Like a bit of our personality.

598
01:07:11,410 --> 01:07:13,503
I don't know what you mean.

599
01:07:16,215 --> 01:07:19,911
I remember, in the newspaper...

600
01:07:19,985 --> 01:07:25,446
a man lost his arm in an accident
and wanted to have it buried.

601
01:07:25,524 --> 01:07:28,015
He wanted to do what?

602
01:07:28,093 --> 01:07:31,459
Have it buried in a cemetery.

603
01:07:31,529 --> 01:07:34,794
- He must have been nuts.
- The authorities refused.

604
01:07:35,900 --> 01:07:39,199
The arm was cremated,
and that was that.

605
01:07:39,270 --> 01:07:41,738
Where did this happen--
in France?

606
01:07:42,972 --> 01:07:47,909
I wonder if they refused
to give him the ashes.

607
01:07:47,977 --> 01:07:51,640
And if so, by what right?

608
01:07:51,714 --> 01:07:54,182
Haven't you got anything
more cheerful to talk about?

609
01:08:04,459 --> 01:08:06,393
All right. That'll do.

610
01:08:10,831 --> 01:08:12,128
Don't worry.

611
01:08:23,577 --> 01:08:25,807
Tell me--

612
01:08:25,879 --> 01:08:30,282
At what precise moment...

613
01:08:30,350 --> 01:08:34,946
does an individual stop being
who he thinks he is?

614
01:08:36,155 --> 01:08:39,921
You know,
I don't like complications.

615
01:08:39,992 --> 01:08:42,222
You cut off my arm, right?

616
01:08:42,294 --> 01:08:46,526
I say me and my arm.

617
01:08:46,599 --> 01:08:48,930
You cut off my other arm.

618
01:08:49,000 --> 01:08:52,265
I say me and my two arms.

619
01:08:56,975 --> 01:09:01,139
Take out my stomach, my kidneys--

620
01:09:01,212 --> 01:09:03,679
assuming that were possible.

621
01:09:05,015 --> 01:09:08,348
And I say
me and my intestines.

622
01:09:11,221 --> 01:09:12,813
Follow me?

623
01:09:16,826 --> 01:09:20,660
And now,
if you cut off my head...

624
01:09:20,730 --> 01:09:23,290
would I say...

625
01:09:23,366 --> 01:09:27,734
me and my head,
or me and my body?

626
01:09:30,171 --> 01:09:34,767
What right has my head
to call itself "me"?

627
01:09:38,213 --> 01:09:39,805
What right?

628
01:10:49,044 --> 01:10:50,379
Oh, God.

629
01:11:16,970 --> 01:11:18,597
Monsieur Trelkovsky?

630
01:11:24,010 --> 01:11:26,637
Stay! Stay, Mirza, stay.

631
01:11:28,847 --> 01:11:31,714
You were out all night, huh?

632
01:11:31,784 --> 01:11:36,118
Yes, I had to stay with my uncle.

633
01:11:36,188 --> 01:11:38,122
He isn't well.

634
01:11:39,223 --> 01:11:42,158
I'll tell Madame Dioz
you're back.

635
01:11:42,226 --> 01:11:44,456
Madame Dioz?

636
01:11:44,529 --> 01:11:46,360
Who's Madame Dioz?

637
01:11:47,598 --> 01:11:51,364
This isn't for me. Look!

638
01:12:06,682 --> 01:12:11,085
"Best wishes from the Louvre.
Georges Badar."

639
01:13:26,456 --> 01:13:29,584
I should like to have
a word with you, monsieur.

640
01:13:29,659 --> 01:13:31,718
Please, come in, madame.

641
01:13:33,663 --> 01:13:36,130
I am Madame Dioz.

642
01:13:39,101 --> 01:13:40,534
Pleased to meet you.

643
01:13:40,602 --> 01:13:44,902
This is why I've come to see you.
Please read it.

644
01:13:44,973 --> 01:13:49,500
It is a petition against
the unspeakable Madame Gaderian.

645
01:13:49,577 --> 01:13:54,674
She's gone too far this time.
We've got to do something about it.

646
01:13:54,749 --> 01:13:59,516
Look. Even Monsieur Zy
has signed. There.

647
01:13:59,587 --> 01:14:03,078
Who is this Madame Gaderian?
I don't know her.

648
01:14:03,156 --> 01:14:07,286
You mean, you don't know her? Who
do you think makes all that noise?

649
01:14:07,360 --> 01:14:10,261
It is her, my dear young man.
It is her.

650
01:14:10,330 --> 01:14:14,960
Do you know she does her washing up
in the middle of the night?

651
01:14:15,035 --> 01:14:17,935
And she whistles
at the same time.

652
01:14:18,003 --> 01:14:21,495
Now, does a civilized person
behave like that?

653
01:14:21,574 --> 01:14:23,474
No, I suppose not.

654
01:14:23,542 --> 01:14:27,478
Well, go on then, sign. It's simply
a question of solidarity.

655
01:14:27,546 --> 01:14:33,211
She's making life impossible for--
for the other tenants.

656
01:14:33,284 --> 01:14:36,481
Is she the one who lives
with a disabled daughter?

657
01:14:37,722 --> 01:14:40,122
Disabled? No.

658
01:14:40,191 --> 01:14:43,523
She has a boy--
a horrible, noisy brat...

659
01:14:43,594 --> 01:14:48,429
who's always playing skittles
or God knows what in the corridor.

660
01:14:48,498 --> 01:14:53,435
Are you sure? Are you certain
she doesn't have a young daughter?

661
01:14:54,538 --> 01:14:58,906
I don't know
what goes on in their lair.

662
01:14:58,975 --> 01:15:01,307
Ask the concierge.

663
01:15:05,181 --> 01:15:08,274
I'm sorry.
I'm not signing any petition.

664
01:15:09,918 --> 01:15:12,250
This woman has
never bothered me.

665
01:15:12,320 --> 01:15:15,153
I've never seen her
or even heard of her.

666
01:15:16,491 --> 01:15:19,892
What apartment does
she live in anyway?

667
01:15:19,961 --> 01:15:23,157
I shall make a note
of your attitude.

668
01:15:23,230 --> 01:15:25,858
I can see what we're
dealing with here.

669
01:15:25,933 --> 01:15:28,697
Everyone for himself,
and never mind anyone else, hmm?

670
01:15:28,769 --> 01:15:30,396
Not at all. I--

671
01:15:30,471 --> 01:15:34,167
I know your type exactly,
like that man opposite...

672
01:15:34,240 --> 01:15:37,368
right up until the day he was
struck down with paralysis.

673
01:15:37,443 --> 01:15:41,311
Then his neighbors let him
stew in his own juice.

674
01:15:41,381 --> 01:15:45,181
By all means,
do whatever you think best.

675
01:15:46,252 --> 01:15:48,651
But I warn you:

676
01:15:48,720 --> 01:15:51,746
Don't come whining to me later.

677
01:15:58,597 --> 01:16:00,530
Bastards!

678
01:16:08,673 --> 01:16:11,164
What do they want me to do--
drop dead?

679
01:16:15,578 --> 01:16:18,843
With my wife,
it's always the same old--

680
01:16:29,758 --> 01:16:31,817
It's for me.

681
01:17:26,344 --> 01:17:28,938
<i>It's no use
playing innocent with me.</i>

682
01:17:29,013 --> 01:17:33,346
I've heard a good deal about you,
Monsieur Trelkovsky.

683
01:17:33,417 --> 01:17:36,944
You specialize in breaches
of the peace at night.

684
01:17:37,020 --> 01:17:40,581
I'm quite amazed, Inspector.

685
01:17:40,657 --> 01:17:43,091
No one has said anything to me.

686
01:17:45,828 --> 01:17:47,430
I'm certainly not
in the habit of making noise.

687
01:17:47,430 --> 01:17:48,761
I'm certainly not
in the habit of making noise.

688
01:17:48,831 --> 01:17:50,765
I have very few friends,
and I never entertain.

689
01:17:50,833 --> 01:17:55,668
I'm not interested in your stories.
I have other things to do.

690
01:17:55,738 --> 01:18:01,004
But I keep getting complaints. It's
my duty to maintain law and order.

691
01:18:01,075 --> 01:18:03,100
So I say it once and for all:

692
01:18:03,178 --> 01:18:05,339
Stop whatever it is
you're doing at night.

693
01:18:08,082 --> 01:18:11,414
- Trelkovsky-- is that Russian?
- Polish.

694
01:18:12,753 --> 01:18:14,687
So you're not French.

695
01:18:14,755 --> 01:18:19,249
- I am a French citizen.
- Let me see your identity card.

696
01:18:31,637 --> 01:18:33,901
It's in a very poor state.

697
01:18:35,441 --> 01:18:38,034
But you haven't registered
your change of address.

698
01:18:39,711 --> 01:18:42,339
15 Rue Sedan. Where is this?

699
01:18:42,414 --> 01:18:45,178
I'm terribly sorry.
I'll do it at once.

700
01:18:47,419 --> 01:18:50,319
You'd be well advised to.

701
01:18:50,387 --> 01:18:54,585
Right. This time I shall
close my eyes to the whole business.

702
01:18:54,658 --> 01:18:57,354
Just make sure I don't hear
any more about you.

703
01:18:57,428 --> 01:18:59,919
I won't have some little
troublemaker disturbing the peace.

704
01:18:59,997 --> 01:19:01,931
Thank you very much, Inspector.

705
01:19:04,100 --> 01:19:06,034
Good-bye.

706
01:19:22,518 --> 01:19:24,452
Good afternoon, madame.

707
01:19:24,520 --> 01:19:27,683
I would like to know who registered
a complaint against me.

708
01:19:29,525 --> 01:19:32,049
Do you know who it was?

709
01:19:32,126 --> 01:19:36,790
If you didn't make so much noise,
there wouldn't be any complaints.

710
01:19:36,864 --> 01:19:38,855
Was there a petition?

711
01:19:41,402 --> 01:19:45,599
Was it that woman that came to
see me the other day-- Madame Dioz?

712
01:19:47,274 --> 01:19:50,869
You only have
yourself to blame.

713
01:19:50,944 --> 01:19:52,878
Did you sign it?

714
01:20:28,011 --> 01:20:32,107
That's it. She's won.
They've all signed it.

715
01:20:32,182 --> 01:20:35,014
All except you, monsieur.
I've come to thank you.

716
01:20:35,084 --> 01:20:37,678
You're a good person.

717
01:20:37,753 --> 01:20:39,812
I don't like to get
mixed up in this kind of thing.

718
01:20:39,889 --> 01:20:43,848
Nonsense. No, you are a good person.
I can see it in your eyes.

719
01:20:46,095 --> 01:20:48,119
I got even with them...

720
01:20:48,196 --> 01:20:51,632
and the concierge too:
she's as bad as all of them.

721
01:20:51,700 --> 01:20:55,636
I paid them back all right.
They gave me the idea.

722
01:20:55,704 --> 01:20:58,229
Do you know what I did?

723
01:20:58,306 --> 01:21:01,036
I did it on the staircase...

724
01:21:01,109 --> 01:21:04,236
in front of everyone's door.

725
01:21:05,946 --> 01:21:07,675
It's their own fault.

726
01:21:07,748 --> 01:21:11,479
They gave me the idea.
I didn't do it by your door.

727
01:21:11,552 --> 01:21:13,986
I don't want to cause you
any trouble.

728
01:21:15,388 --> 01:21:17,879
- How long ago?
-Just now.

729
01:21:19,258 --> 01:21:22,785
I would love to see their faces
when they find out.

730
01:21:24,397 --> 01:21:26,865
It serves them right,
all of them.

731
01:21:26,933 --> 01:21:29,196
But they--
they'll say I did it!

732
01:21:29,267 --> 01:21:31,258
Good night, monsieur.
Sleep well.

733
01:26:59,038 --> 01:27:00,972
Hey, look.

734
01:28:05,800 --> 01:28:08,098
They want to drive me
to suicide.

735
01:28:15,342 --> 01:28:18,937
All right.
I'll show them.

736
01:29:31,112 --> 01:29:33,477
Just shoes.

737
01:29:35,015 --> 01:29:39,543
Simply-- Where in the world
did you find them?

738
01:29:46,993 --> 01:29:49,655
Eighty francs.
You're kidding.

739
01:29:49,729 --> 01:29:51,663
Supermarket, yes.

740
01:29:58,203 --> 01:30:01,639
She's not as young
as she thinks she is.

741
01:30:06,044 --> 01:30:08,569
Beautiful, beautiful.

742
01:30:08,647 --> 01:30:10,740
Adorable.

743
01:30:12,616 --> 01:30:15,847
A goddess, divine.

744
01:30:31,067 --> 01:30:33,001
I think I'm pregnant.

745
01:32:10,090 --> 01:32:11,955
Monsters!

746
01:32:15,696 --> 01:32:19,530
They'll never turn me
into Simone Choule.

747
01:32:19,600 --> 01:32:20,862
Never!

748
01:32:23,169 --> 01:32:24,602
Monsieur Trelkovsky.

749
01:32:27,907 --> 01:32:31,308
Do you remember the conditions on
which I let you have this apartment?

750
01:32:31,377 --> 01:32:33,470
I most certainly do,
Monsieur Zy.

751
01:32:33,546 --> 01:32:35,479
May I know what you're
referring to?

752
01:32:35,547 --> 01:32:37,515
I'm referring to what I said
about women.

753
01:32:37,582 --> 01:32:39,379
Oh, yes, of course.

754
01:32:39,451 --> 01:32:41,817
Then why do you
bring them around here?

755
01:32:43,722 --> 01:32:47,249
What? I never brought
any women around here.

756
01:32:47,325 --> 01:32:49,258
I know what I'm talking about.

757
01:32:49,326 --> 01:32:52,420
You had a woman up in your room.
You can't deny it.

758
01:32:53,564 --> 01:32:56,431
I'll turn a blind eye
to it this time...

759
01:32:56,500 --> 01:32:59,230
but this is the last time.

760
01:32:59,303 --> 01:33:01,236
I hope that's clear.

761
01:33:09,445 --> 01:33:11,675
Good morning,
Monsieur Trelkovsky.

762
01:33:24,393 --> 01:33:26,452
Bring me a coffee.

763
01:33:26,528 --> 01:33:28,859
- You don't want a chocolate?
- I just told you, I want a coffee.

764
01:33:28,930 --> 01:33:30,864
But you always have a chocolate.

765
01:33:30,932 --> 01:33:33,992
You always serve me
without asking what I want.

766
01:33:34,068 --> 01:33:37,367
Now, today I am telling you.
I'd like a coffee.

767
01:33:46,947 --> 01:33:50,849
I'm sorry, but the problem is,
you see...

768
01:33:50,917 --> 01:33:54,352
the machine's broken down.

769
01:33:54,420 --> 01:33:56,911
- Sure you won't have a chocolate?
- No!

770
01:33:56,989 --> 01:34:00,789
- Why the hell should I?
- It's nothing to get sore about.

771
01:34:00,860 --> 01:34:03,727
I'll have a glass of red wine.

772
01:34:03,796 --> 01:34:06,492
I suppose you're
out of Gauloises.

773
01:34:06,564 --> 01:34:08,759
That's right.
We've only got Marlboros.

774
01:34:08,833 --> 01:34:10,767
You can keep them.

775
01:34:12,370 --> 01:34:14,565
I know just what you are up to.

776
01:34:14,639 --> 01:34:17,369
Goddamn murderers!

777
01:34:19,210 --> 01:34:22,042
No good looking at me like that.

778
01:34:22,112 --> 01:34:24,945
I know exactly
what your little scheme is.

779
01:34:43,499 --> 01:34:46,695
- What's wrong?
- My boat.

780
01:34:46,768 --> 01:34:50,067
- Which one?
- The red one.

781
01:34:55,310 --> 01:34:58,768
- What's your name?
- Patrick.

782
01:35:03,684 --> 01:35:06,847
And you've lost your boat--
the red one?

783
01:35:08,455 --> 01:35:11,151
Okay, I'll get it back for you.

784
01:35:20,366 --> 01:35:22,425
Filthy little brat!

785
01:36:12,881 --> 01:36:14,143
Mother. Mother!

786
01:36:48,314 --> 01:36:50,317
It's him! He's there!

787
01:37:41,597 --> 01:37:43,224
I'll fight.

788
01:37:45,368 --> 01:37:47,598
I'll fight to the bitter end.

789
01:40:54,008 --> 01:40:55,942
Who is it?

790
01:40:56,010 --> 01:40:58,979
It's me, Trelkovsky.

791
01:41:04,552 --> 01:41:08,647
- Were you sleeping?
- What's the matter?

792
01:41:11,791 --> 01:41:14,624
Sorry to bother you
at this hour of the morning.

793
01:41:14,694 --> 01:41:18,686
Do you mind if I
stayed here for a while?

794
01:41:23,335 --> 01:41:25,269
You're strange.

795
01:41:26,872 --> 01:41:31,808
You must tell me.
I wouldn't mind, really.

796
01:41:31,876 --> 01:41:35,676
No. No, of course
you can stay.

797
01:41:44,589 --> 01:41:48,354
- Look, you're hurt.
- It's nothing, really.

798
01:41:52,162 --> 01:41:55,529
- But it's filthy.
- That's nothing.

799
01:41:55,599 --> 01:41:59,500
Oh, wait, wait.
I think I've got some--

800
01:41:59,568 --> 01:42:01,695
some things here.

801
01:42:19,687 --> 01:42:21,882
How did you do that?

802
01:42:21,956 --> 01:42:24,651
It's them.

803
01:42:24,725 --> 01:42:27,193
Who?

804
01:42:27,260 --> 01:42:29,194
They're trying to kill me.

805
01:42:32,499 --> 01:42:34,694
Drive me to suicide.

806
01:42:34,768 --> 01:42:37,998
What are you talking about?

807
01:42:38,070 --> 01:42:40,061
Who's trying to kill you?

808
01:42:40,139 --> 01:42:43,302
Stella, I've been lying to you.

809
01:42:44,977 --> 01:42:47,810
I'm living in her apartment.

810
01:42:47,880 --> 01:42:50,211
Whose apartment?

811
01:42:50,281 --> 01:42:52,408
Simone's.

812
01:42:52,484 --> 01:42:55,817
I rented Simone Choule's apartment.

813
01:42:57,155 --> 01:43:00,613
- How did you rent it?
- She died because of the neighbors.

814
01:43:02,227 --> 01:43:04,456
It was a plot.

815
01:43:04,528 --> 01:43:07,998
A plot against Simone?
You're completely insane.

816
01:43:08,131 --> 01:43:10,065
I'm not insane. Listen.

817
01:43:10,133 --> 01:43:13,102
They forced her
to commit suicide.

818
01:43:13,169 --> 01:43:15,933
I can prove it.

819
01:43:16,006 --> 01:43:20,271
And they are trying
to do the same thing to me.

820
01:43:20,342 --> 01:43:24,244
Everything's ready. They worked it
all out, every detail.

821
01:43:24,313 --> 01:43:27,441
Do you know what
they've been doing to me?

822
01:43:27,516 --> 01:43:29,915
It's--

823
01:43:29,984 --> 01:43:32,646
It's so appalling...

824
01:43:32,720 --> 01:43:36,019
so incredible that
I can hardly tell you...

825
01:43:36,090 --> 01:43:39,218
yet it's true, I swear it.

826
01:43:39,293 --> 01:43:42,819
Oh, tell me.
Tell me. I'm listening.

827
01:43:46,733 --> 01:43:52,000
They've been trying to
turn me into Simone Choule.

828
01:43:54,775 --> 01:43:59,370
There now. I'm your friend.
I'm going to help you.

829
01:43:59,445 --> 01:44:01,572
Come now.

830
01:44:01,647 --> 01:44:06,050
You're exhausted.
Lie down.

831
01:44:09,554 --> 01:44:12,523
I'm going to leave Paris
in a couple of days.

832
01:44:12,590 --> 01:44:17,186
- They'll never find me.
- That's the best thing to do.

833
01:44:18,797 --> 01:44:21,459
You're the only one
I can trust.

834
01:44:21,533 --> 01:44:23,466
Aren't you?

835
01:45:00,836 --> 01:45:03,633
It's me, Stella.

836
01:45:03,704 --> 01:45:05,968
Don't be frightened.

837
01:45:07,408 --> 01:45:10,639
You do recognize me,
don't you?

838
01:45:13,714 --> 01:45:16,307
Sorry.

839
01:45:16,382 --> 01:45:18,475
I was having a nightmare.

840
01:45:18,551 --> 01:45:20,246
I must get to work now.
I'm late.

841
01:45:20,320 --> 01:45:25,223
I'll be back around 8:00.
I've left your breakfast ready.

842
01:45:26,392 --> 01:45:30,327
- I love you.
- And I love you.

843
01:45:32,898 --> 01:45:35,833
I even went out and
bought you some croissants.

844
01:45:38,036 --> 01:45:40,401
Please stay with me.
Don't leave me alone.

845
01:45:40,471 --> 01:45:42,405
Oh, now, listen.
I'm late.

846
01:45:42,473 --> 01:45:45,340
If you want to go out,
just leave the keys under the mat.

847
01:45:45,409 --> 01:45:49,368
I'll get another pair made tomorrow.
We'll each have our own set then.

848
01:45:51,883 --> 01:45:55,443
- Please don't go.
- Don't be naughty now.

849
01:45:55,519 --> 01:45:59,387
You're to be good
and stay here.

850
01:46:00,490 --> 01:46:03,357
You've got everything you need.

851
01:46:03,426 --> 01:46:06,519
If you like, you can go out
and get some fresh air.

852
01:46:06,595 --> 01:46:09,120
I'll bring some food
back this evening.

853
01:46:09,198 --> 01:46:13,760
We'll eat in, or go out
to a restaurant, if you like.

854
01:46:13,836 --> 01:46:15,770
We'll see how you feel.

855
01:46:17,239 --> 01:46:19,366
See you tonight then.

856
01:47:22,733 --> 01:47:24,667
Is anyone there?

857
01:47:55,696 --> 01:47:58,062
Filthy bitch!

858
01:47:59,267 --> 01:48:01,633
They're all in it together.

859
01:48:44,975 --> 01:48:47,967
- Stop here. Stop, stop.
- Hey, what's wrong?

860
01:48:48,045 --> 01:48:51,037
Nothing. I'm getting out.

861
01:49:47,133 --> 01:49:49,600
- Is that all right?
- Yeah.

862
01:50:44,352 --> 01:50:47,515
Thank you, monsieur.
Thank you very much.

863
01:50:57,297 --> 01:50:59,959
Have you got any idea
where I can buy a gun?

864
01:51:01,601 --> 01:51:05,765
- I'll pay good money.
- Get the hell out of here, punk!

865
01:51:05,839 --> 01:51:10,366
- This bugger wants to buy a gun!
- What?

866
01:51:12,911 --> 01:51:14,538
I'll tell the cops,
you little shit!

867
01:51:43,907 --> 01:51:47,967
I told you not to drive so fast.
Now look what's happened.

868
01:52:01,189 --> 01:52:03,214
Monsieur, are you hurt?

869
01:52:03,291 --> 01:52:06,692
People who can't drive should
take taxis, you old jerks.

870
01:52:06,761 --> 01:52:10,458
How dare you say that! My wife
hasn't had an accident in 25 years.

871
01:52:10,532 --> 01:52:13,796
He's right. The guy walked
right under the wheels.

872
01:52:13,867 --> 01:52:16,392
- I saw the whole thing.
- Let me through, please.

873
01:52:16,470 --> 01:52:18,734
Excuse me. Let me through.
Let me through.

874
01:52:18,806 --> 01:52:21,331
Excuse me. Excuse me.
I'm a doctor.

875
01:52:43,628 --> 01:52:45,459
Murderers.

876
01:52:47,666 --> 01:52:51,568
Believe me, my wife and I are
very upset about what has happened.

877
01:52:51,636 --> 01:52:53,899
Please stand back.
On the curb.

878
01:52:53,971 --> 01:52:56,462
- Back.
- Officer. This is how it happened.

879
01:52:56,540 --> 01:53:00,271
Your ID, please.
Yours too, monsieur.

880
01:53:00,344 --> 01:53:03,142
You're very lucky.

881
01:53:03,214 --> 01:53:05,773
Only a few scratches.

882
01:53:05,849 --> 01:53:07,680
Nothing broken.

883
01:53:08,618 --> 01:53:10,677
But you should have an X ray.

884
01:53:15,725 --> 01:53:19,524
It's not serious. A mild case of
delirium tremens, in my opinion.

885
01:53:19,595 --> 01:53:23,258
The driver and her husband made
a statement. They'll drive him home.

886
01:53:23,332 --> 01:53:26,495
Is that all right, Doctor?
Or should I call for an ambulance?

887
01:53:26,568 --> 01:53:29,537
Well, if this gentleman can
manage it, it'd be fine.

888
01:53:29,605 --> 01:53:33,335
We'd be glad to give this poor man
a lift home. Of course.

889
01:53:39,514 --> 01:53:42,415
We'll take you home, huh?

890
01:53:51,224 --> 01:53:53,692
That is preposterous!
No! Please!

891
01:53:55,228 --> 01:53:57,162
- They were trying to kill me.
- Yeah?

892
01:53:57,230 --> 01:53:59,595
They were playing football
with a human head.

893
01:53:59,665 --> 01:54:02,031
I'll give him a shot
of something to calm him down.

894
01:54:02,101 --> 01:54:04,399
No. No injection.

895
01:54:04,470 --> 01:54:06,233
I don't want any injection.

896
01:54:08,140 --> 01:54:10,074
I don't want an injection.

897
01:54:11,242 --> 01:54:13,267
They tried to kill me.

898
01:55:16,336 --> 01:55:18,270
Mirza, quiet down!

899
01:55:21,808 --> 01:55:27,303
Good evening, madam. This gentleman
has had a slight accident.

900
01:55:27,380 --> 01:55:29,973
Nothing serious, though.
Nothing to worry about, but--

901
01:55:30,048 --> 01:55:34,417
- What did he do now?
- Let's get him up to the apartment.

902
01:55:35,621 --> 01:55:37,555
How did it happen?

903
01:55:37,623 --> 01:55:41,150
He sort of jumped out
in front of the car, and--

904
01:55:41,226 --> 01:55:45,059
Luckily my wife
has very good reflexes.

905
01:55:46,998 --> 01:55:50,126
What's going on here?

906
01:55:50,201 --> 01:55:51,828
It's him again.

907
01:55:52,904 --> 01:55:55,236
Oh, that bastard!

908
01:58:12,899 --> 01:58:15,629
Stay. Stay, Mirza.

909
01:58:31,250 --> 01:58:34,150
- What was that?
- Down in the courtyard.

910
01:58:59,909 --> 01:59:03,538
We'd better call an ambulance.
Go get one, quick.

911
01:59:04,880 --> 01:59:06,939
You shouldn't move!

912
01:59:11,187 --> 01:59:13,586
Monsieur, I swear
I am not Simone Choule.

913
01:59:13,655 --> 01:59:15,350
Quick, get him a blanket.

914
01:59:15,423 --> 01:59:18,324
Two suicides in succession.

915
01:59:18,393 --> 01:59:23,888
- It's quite unbelievable.
- Look at his clothes. He's insane.

916
01:59:23,965 --> 01:59:27,456
And we just finished
repairing the roof.

917
01:59:27,534 --> 01:59:31,368
I knew there was something wrong
with him the first time I saw him.

918
01:59:35,843 --> 01:59:40,472
Oh, God, Monsieur Trelkovsky! Be
reasonable. Wait for the ambulance.

919
01:59:59,464 --> 02:00:02,297
You gang of killers!

920
02:00:02,367 --> 02:00:04,800
I'll show you some blood.

921
02:00:08,205 --> 02:00:10,799
You wanted a clean death,
didn't you?

922
02:00:10,875 --> 02:00:13,867
- Be reasonable.
- It's going to be dirty.

923
02:00:15,079 --> 02:00:17,240
Unforgettable.

924
02:00:17,314 --> 02:00:20,146
It was better last time,
wasn't it?

925
02:00:20,216 --> 02:00:22,150
Well, I'm not Simone Choule.

926
02:00:23,820 --> 02:00:25,754
I'm Trelkovsky!

927
02:00:37,099 --> 02:00:40,364
All right, all right.
What's going on?

928
02:00:40,435 --> 02:00:43,404
- A tenant jumped out of a window.
- Again?

929
02:00:43,472 --> 02:00:46,099
- You must get them wholesale.
- Where is he now?

930
02:00:46,174 --> 02:00:48,574
He's gone back up
to his apartment.

931
02:00:48,643 --> 02:00:51,908
I think he must have had
some kind of a brainstorm.

932
02:00:51,979 --> 02:00:53,503
He's gonna jump again!

933
02:00:54,615 --> 02:00:58,106
- Tuck into the gallery.
- Take it easy! Don't move!

934
02:00:58,185 --> 02:01:01,780
- We'll come up and get you, okay?
- Be reasonable now.

935
02:01:01,855 --> 02:01:04,756
- Please! It's enough.
- Why is this happening?

936
02:01:06,159 --> 02:01:10,959
- Oh, God, no.
- Don't do anything silly!

937
02:01:27,745 --> 02:01:29,838
Are you a friend of hers?

938
02:01:30,582 --> 02:01:32,209
Oh, I'm sorry.

939
02:01:35,820 --> 02:01:38,754
What on earth
could have happened?

940
02:01:38,822 --> 02:01:41,347
Why would she do
a thing like that?

941
02:01:43,293 --> 02:01:47,491
To tell you the truth,
I'm not a friend of hers at all.

942
02:01:47,564 --> 02:01:50,361
I hardly know her,
actually, but--

943
02:01:53,102 --> 02:01:55,036
Simone.

944
02:01:58,507 --> 02:02:01,704
You do recognize me,
don't you?

945
02:02:01,777 --> 02:02:05,473
It's me, Stella.

946
02:02:05,547 --> 02:02:08,516
Your friend, Stella.

947
02:02:08,583 --> 02:02:10,551
Don't you recognize me?

948
